dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Taibu b Utseya 18 (29b 1x4 0x6 28m) SR: 62.06

dismissalComment.html: Utseya takes out Virat. Nice work from Taibu. It was a flighted delivery that turned in  from outside off, Virat tried to work it to the on side, the ball hits the edge and bounds off Taibu's shoulder and he catches it on the rebound.

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina run out (Blignaut) 3 (5b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: Raina is run out They had some problem in the last over as well. Raina is out this time ... He pushed it to right of short extra cover for a single. It was his call but Rohit thinks its too risky call to accept and stays put. Raina turns back and even dives but can't beat the direct hit from Blignaut. Raina has to go.

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma run out (Chigumbura/Cremer) 13 (25b 0x4 0x6 34m) SR: 52

dismissalComment.html: Rohit is run out Loverly drama there. Zimbabwe are calling all the shots here. It was pushed towards midwicket and Rohit isoff for the single but Jadeja sends him back. Rohit turns, Chigumbura swoops on the ball and throws it to the bowler who breaks the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c Vijay b Ojha 74 (90b 6x4 1x6 103m) SR: 82.22

dismissalComment.html: Taylor has holed out. He went down the track and ended up chipping it to long-off. He has played a few lovely chip shots today but they were usually over mid-on. This time he sliced it to long-off. Fine innings, though. He has put Zimbabwe on course to victory here

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Kohli b Jadeja 66 (86b 4x4 2x6 125m) SR: 76.74

dismissalComment.html: Stunner from Virat Kohli. It was pulled to right of midwicket where Virat dives full stretch to take it. Masakadza falls after a fab effort. Together with Tayor, he has put Zimbabwe on a cruise mode here

batsmen.shot: on side drive on front foot

image.caption: Greg Lamb
image.longCaption: Greg Lamb portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

commentTextItems.html: Dinda's fascination with his slower ones continue. They can be picked so early and easily and this one has been pulled away to the boundary. Zimbabwe have been clinical, professional and have crushed India here.

commentPostTextItems.html: Impressive. Professional. Thumping win. And Zimbabwe have beaten India in successive ODIs for the first time ever. And Suresh Raina had said on the eve of the tour that "team had no weakness". Oh well...!
Avi: "It looks that In all the captaincy tension, Raina forget the difference in strength and weakness... i think he meant to say "Team has no strength".. :D"
This is Zimbabwe's third biggest in terms of balls remaining, excluding wins against minnows. \

Jambe: "With all due respect to all other comments, i don't think India lost because they are a weaker side. remember how the same team easily swept Sri lanka aside not many days ago. Credit should go to Zimbabwe today because, as the commentary below says, they showed up, were professional and clinical in their play today."
Please wait for the quotes from the post-match ceremony

Suresh Raina: "We didn't bat well. We should have probably scored 260-270.. they bowled well. We are not getting a good partnerships from the openers. We have to learn from it. They [the openers] didn't get runs in last two games. Over all we haven't batted well. Sri Lanka are a good side. Let's hope we play well."

"Elton Chigumbura:" It's a good comeback after the last game. Our bowlers bowled well, esp Blignaut. 10 overs for around 22 runs was outstanding. It was just a matter of opening partnership after that which they gave. All the rest of the bowlers bowled well. We wanted to get a good foundation and it was going to be easy to go after the bonus point after that."

Man of the Match is Brendon Taylor: "I am very happy with this performance after our dismal effort against Sri lanka. Batting with Hamilton, I am always relaxed. He is a powerful hitter. For some reason I was ahead of him today! Consistency has been my biggest problem. If I can get another good knock, I would be happy."
That's it from us. Thanks for logging on.

dismissalComment.html: And after all that plodding and meandering around .. he is gone now..  Suddenly, against the run of play, he rushed down the track and tried to play the big off drive. The ball was a drifter; it floated away from the bat and Taibu did the rest. A strangle little innings is over.

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu
image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Taibu b Utseya 18 (29b 1x4 0x6 28m) SR: 62.06

dismissalComment.html: Utseya takes out Virat. Nice work from Taibu. It was a flighted delivery that turned in  from outside off, Virat tried to work it to the on side, the ball hits the edge and bounds off Taibu's shoulder and he catches it on the rebound.

headshotImage.caption: Andy Blignaut player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Andy Blignaut player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina run out (Blignaut) 3 (5b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: Raina is run out They had some problem in the last over as well. Raina is out this time ... He pushed it to right of short extra cover for a single. It was his call but Rohit thinks its too risky call to accept and stays put. Raina turns back and even dives but can't beat the direct hit from Blignaut. Raina has to go.

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma run out (Chigumbura/Cremer) 13 (25b 0x4 0x6 34m) SR: 52

dismissalComment.html: Rohit is run out Loverly drama there. Zimbabwe are calling all the shots here. It was pushed towards midwicket and Rohit isoff for the single but Jadeja sends him back. Rohit turns, Chigumbura swoops on the ball and throws it to the bowler who breaks the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

image.caption: Ray Price
image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Yusuf Pathan lbw b Price 15 (25b 0x4 1x6 38m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: Dead plumb in front! Ray Price gets yet another international wicket with his arm ball. It landed just outside off and skidded in towards middle. Yusuf was pushing forward to defend but the bat was well outside the line of the delivery.

headshotImage.longCaption: Amit Mishra player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Amit Mishra player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Amit Mishra player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Amit Mishra c Coventry b Cremer 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: For a moment Mishra had transformed to Bravo. He sashayed down the track and played that stylish whippy lofted on drive that Bravo does so well. But of course its just Mishy. It doesn't cover much distance and the long-on fielder ran in to collect that.

image.caption: Greg Lamb
image.longCaption: Greg Lamb portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Ashok Dinda c Taylor b Lamb 16 (17b 1x4 0x6 30m) SR: 94.11

dismissalComment.html: And some one takes a catch. Finally. Taylor it is. It was the mis-hit slog and Taylor ran in from deep midwicket to collect it

headshotImage.caption: Andy Blignaut player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Andy Blignaut player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja c Masakadza b Blignaut 51 (72b 3x4 2x6 100m) SR: 70.83

dismissalComment.html: banged in short and Jadeja flat-bats it straight to long-off. He hung around in middle, got a fifty and pushed India towards 200

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Kohli b Jadeja 66 (86b 4x4 2x6 125m) SR: 76.74

dismissalComment.html: Stunner from Virat Kohli. It was pulled to right of midwicket where Virat dives full stretch to take it. Masakadza falls after a fab effort. Together with Tayor, he has put Zimbabwe on a cruise mode here

headshotImage.caption: M Vijay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: M Vijay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c Vijay b Ojha 74 (90b 6x4 1x6 103m) SR: 82.22

dismissalComment.html: Taylor has holed out. He went down the track and ended up chipping it to long-off. He has played a few lovely chip shots today but they were usually over mid-on. This time he sliced it to long-off. Fine innings, though. He has put Zimbabwe on course to victory here
